guzheng and chinese music ensemble arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe featured archive gallery guzheng and chinese music ensemble started as a student initiated course guzheng and chinese music ensemble now is a regular three quarter series class offered by the music department n 2005 jessica yee 06 a priority resident at kimball hall stanford's arts focus house started a student initiated course in guzheng a traditional chinese musical instrument the course was very popular and taught by local instructor daisy you in 2007 the class became an official course offering through the music department and with the help of sica was able to purchase high quality instruments for the course and ensemble the class is taught as a three quarter series and consists of six to eight students students learn basic guzheng techniques and perform at least once a quarter with a larger recital in the spring students without any background in guzheng are welcome and encouraged to learn shortly after the creation of the guzheng class it became apparent that there was large student interest in playing other chinese instruments such as erhu yangqin and pipa thus the birth of the chinese music ensemble the chinese music ensemble joins the guzheng ensemble for their spring recital music department website alvin chow home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
